sec.p:
Specimens of 
Pulvinaria
species were collected from branches or leaves and were either stored dry in envelopes or preserved in 75% ethanol. Slide mounts were prepared using the method described by 
Hodgson & Henderson (2000)
. An Olympus BH-2 stereoscopic microscope was used to prepare the taxonomic illustration of the adult female of 
Pulvinaria pistaciae
            sp. n.
(

). Specimens were observed and photographs of ventral tubular ducts of young adult females (

) were taken using an EVOS digital inverted microscope. The photographs were improved using Adobe Photoshop CS6 (Adobe Systems Incorporated Inc, SanJose, 
USA
). All measurements were made using NIT-Elements D software (New Imaging Technologies Inc, Paris, 
France
) and are given in either micrometers (μm) or millimeters (mm). The slide-mounted material is deposited at Northwest A & F University (
NWAFU
).

